OL,3,CWhy your chocolate eggs may be more
OL,4,Cexpensive this Easter
OL,6,FAround 60% of the world's cocoa comes
OL,7,Ffrom West Africa, more specifically
OL,8,FGhana and Cote D'Ivoire, but many
OL,9,Fcocoa producing countries have been
OL,10,Fimpacted by climate change, crop
OL,11,Fdiseases and poor investment.
OL,13,FVhari Russell, a Food Marketing expert
OL,14,Fdescribed cocoa as "a commodity
OL,15,Fproduct that is held with traders".
OL,17,F"Companies will buy huge quantities of
OL,18,Fcocoa months in advance suspecting it
OL,19,Fwill be the right quality which
OL,20,Fincreases the price," she said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
